# Vendored npm dependencies (website playground/graph explorer). Their bundled
# READMEs and CHANGELOGs are third-party markdown we neither own nor format.
node_modules/

# Claude Code session worktrees: full repo checkouts owned by other sessions.
# A root-scoped markdownlint walk must never check them.
.claude/

# Generated Markdown. Derived from the Go source tree by content-generate (module
# reference, spell docs, manpages, knowledge) or emitted into a gen/ tree by the docs
# render. It is drift-gated by its own generators, not hand-authored, so a prose linter
# must not gate it - a rule fix belongs in the generator, not the output.
**/gen/
docs/reference/buzz/
docs/reference/manpage/
docs/concepts/spells/
docs/concepts/spells.md
docs/concepts/knowledge.md
CHANGELOG.md

# The AGENTS.md section template is embedded into a larger AGENTS.md, so it intentionally
# starts at "## magus" - the first-line-h1 rule does not apply to a fragment.
cmd/magus/agents-section.md
